Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle at neck join. Circular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff; creamy yellow slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) has drawings of several such stamps. Name Ion. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0369.29?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0471)
